      "chapter": null,
      "original": "μήτε Κιθαιρῶνʼ ὄσσοισιν ἐγώ ,",
      "translation": "nor I see Kithairon with my eyes , nor where a memorial of a thyrsos has been dedicated ; let these concern other Bacchae ."
    },
    {
      "id": "1388",
      "label": "Section 1388",
      "chapter": null,
      "original": "πολλαὶ μορφαὶ τῶν δαιμονίων ,",
      "translation": "Many are the forms of divine things , and the gods bring to pass many things unexpectedly ;"
    },
    {
      "id": "1390",
      "label": "Section 1390",
      "chapter": null,
      "original": "καὶ τὰ δοκηθέντʼ οὐκ ἐτελέσθη ,",
      "translation": "what is expected has not been accomplished , but the god has found out a means for doing things unthought of . So too has this event turned out ."
    }
